<paragraph id="8BFA7D72A943313EFF44F84249EFFF23" blockId="0.[136,1452,1992,2091]" lastBlockId="1.[136,1452,158,221]" lastPageId="1" lastPageNumber="90" pageId="0" pageNumber="89">
<taxonomicName id="4C4506F1A943313FFF44F84248C6F81C" authorityName="F. H. Kurniawan, Yudistira &amp; Mustaqim" authorityYear="2022" box="[136,468,1992,2018]" class="Liliopsida" family="Orchidaceae" genus="Bulbophyllum" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asparagales" pageId="0" pageNumber="89" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="sungaiutikense">
<emphasis id="B931A160A943313FFF44F84248C6F81C" box="[136,468,1992,2018]" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="89">Bulbophyllum sungaiutikense</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is similar to 
<taxonomicName id="4C4506F1A943313FFDBCF8434ACCF81C" authority="Wood &amp; Lamb" authorityName="Wood &amp; Lamb" box="[624,990,1992,2018]" class="Liliopsida" family="Orchidaceae" genus="Bulbophyllum" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asparagales" pageId="0" pageNumber="89" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="nabawanense">
<emphasis id="B931A160A943313FFDBCF8434A3BF81C" box="[624,809,1992,2018]" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="89">B. nabawanense</emphasis>
Wood &amp; Lamb
</taxonomicName>
in 
<bibRefCitation id="EFD40083A943313FFBCBF8424C1BF81C" author="Chan, C. L. &amp; Lamb, A. &amp; Shim, P. S. &amp; Wood, J. J." box="[1031,1289,1992,2019]" pageId="0" pageNumber="89" refId="ref2379" refString="Chan, C. L., Lamb, A., Shim, P. S. &amp; Wood, J. J. (1994) Orchids of Borneo: introduction and a selection of species. Bentham-Moxon Trust, Royal Botanic Gardens, Kew, 352 pp." type="book" year="1994">
Chan 
<emphasis id="B931A160A943313FFB87F8434D6DF81C" box="[1099,1151,1992,2018]" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="89">et al</emphasis>
. (1994: 73)
</bibRefCitation>
, but differs in having tetragonal lateral sepals with more elongate triangular apical part and length per width ratio of 2.4−2.6 (vs. triangular, apex acute, length per width ratio 1.3−1.4), petal with an elongate acuminate apex (vs. acute), labellum longer (length per width ratio 2.7−3.2 vs 1.0−1.3), caudate (vs. acute to obtuse) and verrucose surface (vs. somewhat wrinkled).
</paragraph>
<caption id="DF3A2DFAA942313EFF44F8124DB9F7E4" ID-DOI="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6501462" ID-Zenodo-Dep="6501462" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6501462/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="90" startId="1.[136,229,1944,1966]" targetBox="[183,1404,242,1917]" targetPageId="1">
